g.text: These are based on organic compounds (pigments
and resins). Applied at much lower temperatures and
set through drying under moderate heat (typically
between 60°C and 80°C), they maintain very vivid
colors true to the original pigments.
Ceramic colors and organic colors applied to glass have diﬀerent chromatic renderings due to their
diﬀerent chemical compositions and the processes of application and ﬁring.
